title: Syllabus mentioned in ERP
text: Prerequisite: CY30103 Ideal synthesis; fundamentals of retrosynthesis, symmetry, stereochemistry, conformation analysis, molecular mechanics, stereocontrol, ring formation, reactivity, selectivity, catalysis, organometalic reactions. Functional group transformations, umpolung and protecting groups. Synthetic strategies and selected total syntheses Textbook: M. B. Smith, Organic Synthesis. F. A. Carey and R. J Sundberg, Advanced Organic Chemistry, Part B.
